(secondQuint)Behavioral Economic Approaches to Increase Colorectal Cancer Screening.

 This is an RCT aimed at testing different population-based approaches to increasing colorectal cancer screening.

 The investigators will randomize a cohort of employees between the ages of 50-64 to 3 arms of email communications: a.

) Usual email communication; b.

) Active choice- usual care + the ability to pre-commit directly through a web form; c.

) Financial incentive- usual care + active choice + financial incentive for completion.

